item.title: Live On!
item.description: You tried it so hard again and again But all you can do now is crying in the rain Your castles are fallen, your heroes are few And now you’re looking for someone to believe in you Impossible is nothing, I know for sure And for the deepest heartache there is a cure Impossible is nothing, I want you to know No matter how you suffered now all you gotta do is live on Some river are flowing through the desert heat Some candles keep burning, even in the wind Away hesitation, just do what is true And let me be someone to believe in you Impossible is nothing, I want you to know To matter how you suffered now all you gotta do is live on Live on, live on Live on, live on Live on, live on Live on, live on
